                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCellHeading">Nightmares of mine...</td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCellHeading">
                                 <p align="right"><i>By Richard Vowles,
                                       9 February 2004</i></p>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCell">I came across this book as a recommendation from those who run Horror oriented games and purchased it on eBay - it is out
                                 of print by I.C.E still sell it. It is really the very best "how to" roleplaying book that I have read - it covers all of
                                 the details you would need to know about how to write and run an excellent horror based scenario. It has no game specifics
                                 in it, and mentions are a wide range of different roleplaying games. If you are interested in it, it can be picked up from
                                 I.C.E's store at <a href="http://store.ironcrown.com/detail.jsp?itemId=2023&amp;category=10099" target="_blank">this location.</a></td>
                           </tr>
                        </table><br>
                        
                        
